articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An initiative by the United States to increase electricity supply in Africa has been dismantled by U.S. President Donald Trump's administration after more than a decade of work, Bloomberg News reported on Wednesday, citing people familiar with the matter.
articles.title: Trump ends US initiative to boost electricity access in Africa, Bloomberg News reports

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's military has set up a drill zone for "shooting training" about 40 nautical miles (74 km) off Taiwan's southwest coast without prior notification, the island's defence ministry said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Taiwan flags China's 'shooting' drills off  southwest coast

articles.author: Steve Holland, Kanishka Singh
articles.description: Trump told reporters he will replace the "EB-5" immigrant investor visa program, which allows foreign investors of large sums of money that create or preserve U.S. jobs to become permanent residents, with a so-called "gold card."
articles.title: Trump floats $5 million 'gold card' as a route to US citizenship

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The U.S. and Ukraine have agreed on the terms of a draft minerals deal central to Kyiv's push to win Washington's support as President Donald Trump seeks to rapidly end the war with Russia, two sources with knowledge of the matter said on Tuesday.
articles.title: US, Ukraine agree to terms of critical minerals deal

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Pope Francis, in critical condition battling double pneumonia, had a quiet night in hospital and is resting, the Vatican said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Pope Francis, in critical condition, had quiet night in hospital, Vatican says

articles.author: Tim Cocks
articles.description: Finance ministers and central bankers from the G20 top economies gather in South Africa on Wednesday and Thursday, for a meeting marred by the absence or curtailed attendance of key members and disputes over the main issues of climate, debt and inequality.
articles.title: G20 finance ministers, central bankers to meet amid fractious geopolitics

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The source said the handovers would take place under Egyptian supervision but did not specify the release date.
articles.title: Mediators agree swap of Palestinian prisoners for Israeli hostages' bodies, source says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Kremlin said that preparations were being made for expert-level talks.
articles.title: Kremlin says Russia and US are preparing more talks

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Belgian federal prosecutor said on Wednesday it had started a probe into alleged Chinese hacking of Belgium's intelligence service VSSE in November 2023, confirming an earlier report by Belgian daily Le Soir.
articles.title: Belgian prosecutor probes alleged Chinese hacking of intelligence service

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: International sanctions against Rwanda will reduce the incentive for Kinshasa to engage in peace talks with M23 rebels who have made lightning advances in eastern Congo this year, a proscribed Rwandan minister has said.
articles.title: Rwanda sanctions will undermine push for Congo peace talks, proscribed minister says
